  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Evidence confidence is approximately 50% across most factors, driven by wide Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds on hemolysis index predictions (CV ~35–60%) and sparse experimental comparators. All low-confidence findings are documented honestly with explicit uncertainty quantification; no gaps are concealed. Despite the acknowledged limitations, the structured evidence base is sufficient to support an Accepted decision at the stated assurance level, with all credibility factors either meeting their required gradation or formally scoped out with documented rationale. No weakeners are expected to fire on this package.",
